From 5ad6ba883870d2fc2b8d8a0537c53d685fee06eb Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sophia Hammel <sophiahammel1229@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 16 Jul 2026 11:44:45 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] websiteImprovement: scan history + check-a-URL pages,
 on-device only

Two new website features, both scoped to stay consistent with the
no-server/no-analytics constraints already documented in
website/privacy.html:

- history.html: asks the installed extension for saved sites via
  Chrome's externally_connectable messaging (same-device only, not a
  network request), then runs the extension's own redflags-engine.js
  (synced copy) client-side on the relayed policy text.
- check.html: check a domain without installing the extension. Disclosed
  channel is a direct browser-to-ToS;DR API call (untested for CORS from
  a plain website -- see extension/README.md's open-question section).
  Observed channel reuses the curated tracker_radar_snapshot.json the
  extension itself falls back to.

extension/manifest.json: added a pinned "key" (stable ID
oekejhnandbljcfcemgbjmbmbpjgchha -- private key handed off separately,
not in this repo) and externally_connectable scoped to the site's real
S3 origin plus localhost:8000 for local dev.

New extension/website_bridge_background.js: onMessageExternal listener,
read-only, re-checks sender.origin as defense in depth on top of
manifest scoping, never sends tabId to the website.

No CORS proxy built -- flagged as an explicit open question pending a
real-browser test against api.tosdr.org, since adding one would be this
project's first actual backend component.

extension/README.md and website/privacy.html both updated with the
exact new data flow.
